definitions.definition: To put text on paper using a typewriter.
To enter text or commands into a computer using a keyboard.
To determine the blood type of.
definitions.example: The doctor ordered the lab to type the patient for a blood transfusion.

definitions.definition: To represent by a type, model, or symbol beforehand; to prefigure.
To furnish an expression or copy of; to represent; to typify.
(of a variable, expression, or value) Having a specific data type.
definitions.example: A typed variable can only store one kind of data.

definitions.definition: (of a programming language) In which variables are typed.
